						               													<description>Project Baikal is a collaborative village-building eurogame inspired from tower defence video games.&amp;#10;It is a family-friendly card game for 2 to 4 players, 10+ y.o. and one hour in length.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Project Baikal has an original gameplay where all the players can execute their actions at the same time (no player turn).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Theme&amp;#10;The dark winds of war, famine, plague and catastrophic weather have swept the planet, almost scouring it clean of humanity. &amp;#10;One small enclave still survives though, in a village on the bank of the Lake Baikal in Siberia.&amp;#10;From such humble beginnings the human race can be reborn. And not make the mistakes from the past.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You and your friends are the villagers, keeping out the remnants of the old world and nurturing the hopes of the new. &amp;#10;You will protect the village from wolves, mercenaries and internal pressures like racism and corruption. &amp;#10;You will welcome strangers with needed skills, grow your village and rebuild civilisation anew.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay&amp;#10;From 4 locations, bad events (Sabotage, Wolf pack, Disease, etc) slowly progress towards your newly-formed village.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To defeat those events before they do damage, you will:&amp;#10;- Collect action cards (Move, Meet, Draw, Swap, Build and Give),&amp;#10;- Move to locations (Forest, Lake, Mountain and Road) and&amp;#10;- Encounter those events.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can also acquire good events (old couple, family, dog, etc) who will help to build useful buildings (Town Hall, Lab, Hospital, etc) using gathered resources (Wood and Stone).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You have 6 turns to complete 6 buildings and win the game.&amp;#10;But beware: you can lose instantly if your village takes too much damage!!!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Acknowledgment: Theme written by Ian Triffit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
